204
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:12,780
to continual improvement

205
00:07:12,780 --> 00:07:15,060
because we're always trying
to improve our practices,

206
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:17,190
our activities, and our processes.

207
00:07:17,190 --> 00:07:19,010
And the continual
improvement practice itself

208
00:07:19,010 --> 00:07:20,450
is applied to all of these.

209
00:07:20,450 --> 00:07:22,830
As you can see, the continual
improvement practice

210
00:07:22,830 --> 00:07:25,660
is inside everything we do inside ITIL 4.

211
00:07:25,660 --> 00:07:27,830
We're always trying to
continue to improve.

212
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:30,490
If we go back and look at the
service value chain again,

213
00:07:30,490 --> 00:07:33,610
you see that improve touches
all of those inner cubes

214
00:07:33,610 --> 00:07:36,400
and the engage process
with that purple line.

215
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:39,410
That's because it impacts
every single one of them.

216
00:07:39,410 --> 00:07:40,670
That's the key here.

217
00:07:40,670 --> 00:07:42,770
Continual improvement is
the key to our success

218
00:07:42,770 --> 00:07:45,453
in ITIL 4 because we never
want to stop improving.

